The paper focuses on developing a novel approach to automate the procedure of analyzing test alarms in system and integration testing. This involves exploiting information retrieval techniques to infer test alarm causes based on test logs. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the use of information retrieval techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The development of a prototype and evaluation of the tool on industrial datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the focus on testing in clouds and automation of the procedure suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
